isplaystyle y(t) | =Re​((𝑪​(t)+i​𝑪^​(t))⊤​𝒉​(t)),\\displaystyle=\\mathrm{Re}\\,\\left(({\\bm{C}}(t)+i\\hat{{\\bm{C}}}(t))^{\\top}{\\bm{h}}(t)\\right), |\n\nwhere A​(t)∈ℝA(t)\\in\\mathbb{R} is a scalar and 𝜽​(t),𝑩​(t),𝑩^​(t),𝑪​(t),𝑪^​(t)∈ℝN/2\\bm{\\theta}(t),{\\bm{B}}(t),\\hat{{\\bm{B}}}(t),{\\bm{C}}(t),\\hat{{\\bm{C}}}(t)\\in\\mathbb{R}^{N/2}.\n\nRecall from Prop. [A](#A1 \"Appendix A Exponential-Trapezoidal Discretization ‣ Mamba-3: Improved Sequence Modeling using State Space Principles\"),\n\n|  |  |\n| --- | --- |\n| 𝒉t\\displaystyle{\\bm{h}}\\_{t} | ≈eΔt​(At+i​𝜽t)​𝒉t−1+∫τt−1τte(τt−τ)​(At+i​𝜽t)​(𝑩​(τ)+i​𝑩^​(τ))​x​(τ)​𝑑τ.\\displaystyle\\approx e^{\\Delta\\_{t}(A\\_{t}+i\\bm{\\theta}\\_{t})}\\,{\\bm{h}}\\_{t-1}\\;+\\;\\int\\_{\\tau\\_{t-1}}^{\\tau\\_{t}}e^{(\\tau\\_{t}-\\tau)(A\\_{t}+i\\bm{\\theta}\\_{t})}\\left({\\bm{B}}(\\tau)+i\\hat{{\\bm{B}}}(\\tau)\\right)\\,x(\\tau)\\,d\\tau. |\n\nApplying Prop. [3.1.1](#S3.SS1.SSS1.Px3 \"Exponential-Trapezoidal (Mamba-3). ‣ 3.1.1 Overview of Exponential-Adjusted Discretization ‣ 3.1 Exponential-Trapezoidal Discretization ‣ 3 Methodology ‣ Mamba-3: Improved Sequence Modeling using State Space Principles\") to the above integral, we get\n\n|  |  |  |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| 𝒉t\\displaystyle{\\bm{h}}\\_{t} | =eΔt​(At+i​𝜽t)​𝒉t−1+βt​ei​Δt​𝜽t​(𝑩t−1+i​𝑩^t−1)​xt−1+γt​(𝑩t+i​𝑩^t)​xt,\\displaystyle=e^{\\Delta\\_{t}(A\\_{t}+i\\bm{\\theta}\\_{t})}\\,{\\bm{h}}\\_{t-1}\\;+\\;\\beta\\_{t}\\,e^{i\\Delta\\_{t}\\bm{\\theta}\\_{t}}\\left({\\bm{B}}\\_{t-1}+i\\hat{{\\bm{B}}}\\_{t-1}\\right)x\\_{t-1}\\;+\\;\\gamma\\_{t}\\left({\\bm{B}}\\_{t}+i\\hat{{\\bm{B}}}\\_{t}\\right)x\\_{t}, | (24) |\n\nwhere\n\n|  |\n| --- |\n| αt:=eΔt​At,βt:=(1−λt)​Δt​eΔt​At,γt:=λt​Δt,\\alpha\\_{t}:=e^{\\Delta\\_{t}A\\_{t}},\\qquad\\beta\\_{t}:=(1-\\lambda\\_{t})\\Delta\\_{t}e^{\\Delta\\_{t}A\\_{t}},\\qquad\\gamma\\_{t}:=\\lambda\\_{t}\\Delta\\_{t}, |\n\nSince eΔt​(At+i​𝜽t)=αt​ei​Δt​𝜽te^{\\Delta\\_{t}(A\\_{t}+i\\bm{\\theta}\\_{t})}=\\alpha\\_{t}\\,e^{i\\Delta\\_{t}\\bm{\\